Dorsum — Prodorsum with four pairs of setae and with developed anterior lobes ( Figs. 4A , 6A ). Outer propodosomal lobes rather low, conical, not extending beyond medial of inner lobes. Medial projection well expanded, inner lobes well separated in their distal part with variable obvious incision, 13 (7 – 13) µm in depth (measured from the bottom of the incision between the inner lobes). A horizontal line joining tip of v 2 setae located on the outer lobes crosses v 1 setae about their base, v 1 about two-thirds the size of v 2 . Dorsal body setae spatulate, inserted on tubercles, subequal in length with the exception of v 1 setae far smaller, sacrals ( f 1 , f 2 ) and clunals ( h 1 ) somewhat longer ( Figs. 4A, B ). Dorsocentral setae ( c 1 , d 1 and e 1 ) shorter than distances between consecutive setae (length of holotype and variations of ten paratypes ): v 1 22 (18 – 21); v 2 33 (29 – 32); sc 1 32 (26 – 31); sc 2 26 (22 – 27); c 1 30 (25 – 31); c 2 30 (23 – 29); c 3 27 (22 – 28); d 1 26 (22 – 27); d 2 28 (21 – 28); d 3 26 (23 – 30);
