Dorsum — Prodorsal lobes weakly developed, tubercle like, v 1 very short, spatulate and serrate with spiky appearance, v 2 larger, spatulate and serrate. Other dorsal body setae spatulate with the exception of e 2 sub-spatulate and the following ( e 3 , f 1 , f 2 and h 1 ) elongate, serrate and larger. Lengths of dorsal setae (variations of 4 protonymphs): v 1 7 – 11; v 2 23 – 28; sc 1 22.5 – 25.5; sc 2 18.5 – 20.5; c 1 18 – 21; c 2 17 – 18.5; c 3 16 – 18.5; d 1 16 – 18.5; d 2 20 – 23; d 3 21 – 31;
